Notes from Phase 1 review:

- plugin_state uses state_json TEXT blob instead of individual columns. This is fine — just be consistent. All plugin state reads/writes go through JSON serialization in that column.
- The field is called plugin_id throughout (not “name” or “plugin”). Stay consistent with this.
- Platform DB file is platform.db (not botdata.db). Config uses PLATFORM_DIR (not BOT_DIR).
- The old codebase is still on the server at /opt/15-min-btc-bot/ — read those files for implementation reference. Especially strategy.py (~3,600 lines) and db.py (~3,550 lines) which have battle-tested simulation and query logic.

