1. plugins/btc_15m/strategy.py — the complete Observatory, simulation, and FV model:
- MarketObserver class — accumulates price snapshots, writes observations on market transition, quality tags (full/short/partial/few), health metrics, discard on shutdown
- _simulate_one() — binary option simulation with spread-based slippage (actual bid/ask spread, not flat 1c), absolute timing (early=0s, mid=300s, late=600s), two-snapshot fill delay on entry AND exit, configurable fee_rate, slippage_c parameter
- _brownian_p_yes() — analytical Brownian bridge for model side rule
- run_simulation_batch() — processes observations, runs all strategy variants (4 side rules x 19 entry maxes x variable sell targets x 3 timings), three setup types (global, coarse_regime, hour), time-weighted metrics (14-day half-life), 5-fold rolling walk-forward validation, FDR correction (Benjamini-Hochberg with t-test, 10% threshold), slippage sensitivity (+1c/+2c), fee breakeven, quality split EV. First batch after deploy cleans stale results.
- BtcFairValueModel class — loads probability surface from DB, vol-conditioned surfaces (calm/normal/volatile) with global fallback, distance-weighted interpolation, analytical Brownian bridge fallback, compute_edge() returns recommended side and edge per side, 5-minute cache with auto-reload
- compute_btc_probability_surface() — builds 4 empirical surfaces (all + 3 vol buckets) from observations, 8 distance buckets x 5 time buckets
- compute_feature_importance() — point-biserial correlation ranking of observation features against outcome
- get_recommendation() — hierarchical advisor: coarse_regime -> hour -> global fallback, time-weighted EV ranking, fee resilience filter, OOS validation enforced, min samples from config
- backfill_observation_results() — resolves pending observations via Kalshi API
- analyze_execution_quality(), analyze_correlated_losses() — analytics
